BASIC stack on 6502 stack

• Stack is empty at beginning of program
• GOSUB pushes <ret.lo><ret.hi><0> (3 bytes)
  Return address points to the next BASIC opcode.
• REPEAT pushes <ret.lo><ret.hi><3> (3 bytes)
  Return address points to the first BASIC opcode after REPEAT.
• PROC pushes <ret.lo><ret.hi><6> (5 bytes)
  Return address points to the next BASIC opcode.
• FN pushes <ret.lo><ret.hi> (2 bytes)
  Return address points to the next BASIC opcode.
• FOR pushes <var.lo><var.hi> <end.0><end.1><end.2><end.3><end.4>
                              <step.0><step.1><step.2><step.3><step.4>
                              <ret.lo><ret.hi><2> (15 bytes)
  Return address points to the first BASIC opcode after FOR X = 1 TO 2 STEP 1.
• Expression eval pushes <val.0><val.1><val.2><val.3><val.4> (5 bytes)
• IF pushes <4> (1 byte)
  Marker says we're inside a multi-line IF.
  Scans for ELSE / END IF if the condidion is false (report if DEF, END, EOP found; nested IFs..)
• ELSE pops <4> (required) and pushes <5> (1 byte)
  Scans for END IF if the IF was executed (report if DEF, END, EOP found; nested IFs..)
  Marker says we're inside a multi-line ELSE.
• END IF pops <4> or <5> (required)

