65 cycles per line: 7+6=13 IRQ+RTI -> STA/LDA 6 -> LDA# STA 5 -> total 13+6+5 = 24 cycles
1 line: 24/65 = 36% CPU use, max freq 15720/2 = 7860 (~8B)
2 line: 24/130 = 18% CPU use, max freq = 15720/4 = 3930 (~7B)
4 line: 24/260 = 9% CPU use, max freq = 15720/8 = 1965 (~6B)
8 line: 24/520 = 4.5% CPU use, max freq = 15720/16 = 982 (~5B)
16 line: 24/1040 = 2.3% CPU use, max freq = 15720/32 = 491 (~4B)
This is during normal BASIC execution; bit-bang loops can go much higher.
With the 8-line interrupt, commercial games can play samples.
